The paper deals with the structural controllability of a multi-agent system, which is a topic related to control theory and network science. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also discusses the use of graph theory and indices to characterize the role of individual links and agents, which suggests that it could also be classified under cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of importance measures, which is a topic related to machine learning and artificial intelligence, suggesting that it could also be classified under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
